WindowClientAncestorOrigins.summary: The ancestorOrigins read-only property of the interface is an array of strings listing the origins of all ancestors of the browsing context represented by this WindowClient in reverse order.

remarks.para: The first element in the array is the origin of this window's parent, and the last element is the origin of the top-level browsing context. If this window is itself a top-level browsing context, then ancestorOrigins is an empty array.
